{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require every ICU to have a separate carpark for patients' family to use",
        "additional_details": "The government should make it mandatory that all hospitals with an ICU make a separate carpark so that family of an ICU patient can find a parking space easily so they don\u2019t miss precious time to say goodbye to an end of life ICU patient/family member. No one deserves to not be able to say goodbye to their loved one because they can\u2019t find a parking spot and then risk getting parking tickets if they have had to park somewhere not authorised.",
        "background": "Often people can\u2019t find a space in a hospital car park when they need it most. I believe every ICU should have a separate carpark for patients' family that they can use when they have a short amount of time to say goodbye. This should be gated and the ICU patient name be mentioned for entry.",
